I've gone to this place alot over the past years, all I can say is to stay clear if you aren't trying to have a military cut or soccer douche cut. They don't listen too what you ask for and tend to just do what they want, while taking forever with every cut.

The only decent barbers in there are Edgar or Chuckie (the owner), but they always have a long line of people waiting for them. Edgar is good, but his haircutting skills depend on wether or not he has a hangover or is high at the time (bad). <name>Tina Shafer</name><review>Where do I begin! I had a mouth full of issues and such a fear of dentists due to a couple of really bad past experiances. I came to Dr Khorsand by way of referral and he and the staff are to be recognized for the care and compassion they show thier patients. I had a root canal recently and on my way home from the procedure(I live 45 miles away) the anesthetic wore off and the pain hit. It was so bad I was contiplating going to the emergency room(pain always hits after hours). I checked Dr. Khorsands website and there was an emergency contact listing so I called. I actually spoke to Dr. K directly and he was genuinely concerned, gave me instructions to visit the urgent care next to his office and asked me to call me him back with updates. This kind of care is almost non-existing in this day and age. This Dr and his staff have a huge patient load yet they still go the extra mile. Overall it was a good experience, got my wisdom teeth extracted, quick and easy. I was super nervous and the assistant was sweet and caring. The doctor was also very nice. After pulling out my teeth, which literally took 5 second. Doctor let me go right away, and said he was done and i was ready to go. I wasnt given any instructions about aftercare or what I was suspose to do. I had to google what to do. Im still not sure when I am allowed to eat yet, because google always mix stuff up. Wish i couldve recieved instructions or atleast have them tell me there isnt any restriction. Im sure they must of forget, especially if its busy but this is an important part of procedure. A patient needs to know what to do post extraction, and the best way is by hearing from the doctor that did the extraction. Not from google! All in all, people make mistakes, and well im doing pretty good. So i guess im recovering well.</Review>

< Review>
I've never done a return. I've honestly never really bought clothes online before but I expected Big Bud Press to have a 30 day return window like most places I've seen online. Unfortunately they only have a 14 day window.

I received my package a bit later than the tracking suggested due to the large amounts of delays with holiday/January shipping in general. So I was at 16 days by tracking but still within 14 days since the package arrived on my doorstep.

However when I looked at their website the company acknowledged shipping delays in January and offered store credit in the case of delayed returns. Nice!

I reached asap on a Saturday (there customer service isn't available on the weekends) and received a prompt "no" from their return department on Monday morning, 9am. I explained how there was a delay different then the suggested tracking (I live in a very small town). They said no and highlighted their return policies. When I went to check the policy I had seen for delayed shipping to be turned into store credit the policy it had been removed from their website.

I've gained a lot of weight during quarantine and I am trying to do my best to find pants in a way that is safe. I've struggled with body issues my whole life and I, like many people, am having a difficult time with their body during quarantine.

The 14 day return window is not enough time to safely shop for pants during this period of quarantine, and it seems that BIG BUD Press's return customer service is very unforgiving in regards to all the above mentioned.

I understand how this is from a company stand point, but from a human one, I am a bit hurt. I'll most likely be looking to shop somewhere else in the future.

Edit: Thank you so much for responding! I suppose with so many locations I didn't think of you guys as a small business. You're very popular! I appreciate you looking into my case.

My hope is that you have plans to extend your return window as your company expands. I'm sure that returns are difficult during these times of covid on the business side of thing. I like your business because it incorporates a lot of plus size clothing but I think, as you must know from experience building a plus sized brand, that the reality trying on clothes vs. what they present online can be an especially difficult and unique challenge for plus sized people.

In my opinion the 14 day return window doesn't do much to elevate this difficulty.

My story: Buying these pants was difficult decision for me, finding a good pair of pants that fit when you've dramatically changed sizes is an emotional ordeal outright, especially when struggling with body issues. I know from many of my friends, family, and coworkers that this issue of body image struggle is not unique but in fact very common in the U.S.

I hope that you will hear this story and know that I'm not trying to hurt you or the brand you worked so hard to create (I know public reviews are stressful) but that I just want to offer my feedback as a customer.

Thank you for your time</Review>
<Rate>3<//Rate><time>1611600922755< /time>< response>

On our help page and the packing slip you received in your order it states that we go by 14 days from date of delivery as marked by tracking. The notice you are referring to on our help page was our holiday return policy that ended January 4. Most small brands like ours have shorter return windows-- we try to make that clear everywhere we can-- it's listed on all the email correspondences you received from us as well as physically on the packing slip you receive in your order. It's also on our help page prior to purchasing. You would have had to email us on January 21 to be inside your return window but you emailed on January 23. I know this all may seem arbitrary but we have these policies posted in as many places as we possibly can to help keep everyone as informed as possible."}<//response>

Big Bud is the first company I grew to love before ever owning any of their products which is a bit unconventional, but makes me value my dress even more now because I feel like my hardworking friends made it for me. I would be quite giddy to get to go to one of their stores one day!

< Review>
Ordered twice now from Big Bud, once from their Kickstarter and once from their sample sale! Although I live in Canada and conversion/shipping can be pricey, I really appreciate all they do at this Lil shop to try to accommodate as many people as they possibly can! As many roadblocks as they had during their Kickstarter they always made sure to be as transparent and informative as possible and although I was eager to get my clothing, I understood and appreciated their updates throughout their struggles.

As for the quality of their clothing, it is TO DIE FOR! I honestly have never owned such nice clothing and it makes me feel great to know I'm supporting a small business who really cares for what they do. I own a ringer tee and a shop girl dress and I love them both so much. The fabric is very sturdy and high quality, but incredibly soft. They don't sacrifice comfort for quality or vice versa at all! Everything has a nice stretch to it too, so you're almost better off ordering a size down as its sure to fit snug! I cannot wait to add more of their clothing to my wardrobe in the near future< /Review>

<text>My wife and I were driving north from LA to Marin County to visit family when my Infiniti starting acting up on the I-5 near Coalinga.  The engine was hesitating so badly that I had to exit the highway and look on my smart phone for a nearby Infiniti dealer.  Of course there were none.  The closest dealer was in Merced, and I didn't trust a roadside repair service to identify, and fix, the problem.  I discovered there was a dealer in San Raphael, my destination point, and called there to find out if my car was safe to drive another 100+ miles doing what it was doing.  I spoke with David T. in the Service Dept of Infiniti of Marin.  After David listened to my description of the car's behavior, he said he thought it would be safe for me to drive to the dealership.  When I got to San Raphael I drove straight to the dealership and unloaded my car into my host's vehicle.  A couple of hours later, David called and said the mechanics had identified the problem ( two faulty spark plugs and a bad ignition coil).  After waiting a day for the coil to arrive, I got my car back and drove safely home.  David T. called me several times to keep my updated on the progress of the repairs, and I got back a freshly-washed vehicle to travel home in.  The dealership has a comfortable waiting area and a GREAT coffee machine.  Infiniti of Marin is a quality place to deal with.  Highly recommend.<//text><pics>None</pics>< resp>

< Review>
I recently purchased an Infiniti from a dealer not associated with Infiniti and wanted to have the car formally inspected. Making the appointment on line was very easy. Upon arrival I was greeted in a timely manner. The service manager explained the services, time involved and the cost and sent me on my way. I was offered a space to wait with a tv and coffee. I was informed periodically of the progress on my car during my 2.5 he wait. When the services were completed, I  needed further servicing so I was given directives from the service manager and an explanation about what had been done and a servicing schedule for my car and the range of costs involved for the next maintenance service.   Also, my car was washed. I thought the service was excellent, I will continue to bring my car to this dealership for services as long as I live in this area.<//Review>

I am on my 3rd Infiniti and one of the reasons I keep buying them- in addition to the fact it is a great car- is the service department at Infiniti Marin. Their higher-end used cars are all in an indoor showroom where they're trying to pretend a bunch of used BMWs, Lexuses and Corvettes are Pebble Beach or something. The salesman knew nothing about the car and quoted me a price about $8k more than what it's listed for on their site.

They refuse to do test drives of anything in their pre-owned showroom. I understand "no test drive" rules on new performance cars, but five more miles on an 18,000 mile bimmer isn't going to change anything. It's a used car, not a vintage Ferrari. At the very least they could have informed me of their chickensh*t policies when I booked the appointment and not wasted my time with an hour round trip.<//review>

Never would purchase another Infiniti again nor would recommend anyone to buy one. Not because the brand isnt good or anything but just for the fact that Infiniti would not engage with you if the car is out of warranty and you run into some serious reliability problems.

This is not a bad reflection on Marin Infiniti itself; the service manager who attended to my car was very helpful and she was really sympathetic to my issues. However, the way Infiniti distanced itself from the issue saying it is a older car speaks volume about their customer engagement.

Wear and tear on moving parts are pretty normal on a old car. This is normal. However, I had issues with overheating, TWICE, and both times I was left stranded. Paid a huge amount of money of course but this is not due to usage. This is some inherent issue with the car itself I believe but Infiniti wouldnt even look into it. They are more than happy to keep servicing the car which is a money pit for them anyways. First time, they said something blocked the radiator causing it to blow out and next time, the fans on the radiator was intermittently not working. I dont know how usage can cause issues like this.

Contacting Infiniti directly wasn't any help either. Paying premium money for Infiniti is just a waste since the car isnt reliable at all. If under warranty, go for it. If not, just walk away from the car.<//Text>

< Text>
A couple of my people and I decided to try this place out for calzones considering their ratings. The place is a whole in the wall and they had a decent amount of traffic. I ordered 3 calzones and the total came out to 44 and change, we waited for about 40 minutes and our food finally came out, we ate outside and when I pulled out the calzones and the size was impressively big but they were just wrapped in like a sandwich wrap. Pulling them out we broke them open and oh my goodness it dripped in oil, I poured it out to make it somehow enjoyable, I had the vegetarian, my buddy had the ground beef and cheese, my other had the special and we all had the same issue but theirs not as bad I'm assuming because the beef soaked up the oil. Overall it was a disappointing order for what I paid, I'm sure their other stuff is good (I hope) and the staff was kind. The review was solely on the calzone. Won't be ever ordering that again here!< /Text>

< text>
Cannot say enough good things about this business. They know how to take care of their customers. Have been stopping by for a the best thin New York style pizza for several years. Never disappointed, pizza is always hot and flavorful. The cheese and crust is always the right texture and on point. Owner always made time to conversate as well. Even though I didn't wait long, they gave me some delicious bread with an amazing dipping sauce. I have ordered a full pizza here before and can say I rather have their slices. It's still good but just different in texture and bite.

One gripe is that the slices usually comes out super hot and I would suggest to the owner that it be served on paper plate instead of styrofoam. It is so hot, you can see melted styrofoam. I'm not a Toxicologist, but who knows what sort chemical is coming from that. Didn't stop from eating it still, lol. So good, I would definitely recommend to everyone!</text>

This happens to be the place with the best Italian food in Fresno, I‚Äôve been coming here for years and the reason is it‚Äôs great.  Normally I get the Rigatoni with a spicy red Alfredo sauce.  My wife is a vegetarian and Mike makes it with no meat for me and it is so good.  Another traditional Italian delicacy is the BLT and they have the best one.  And yes it is a traditional Italian and Spartan delicacy.  In 415 BC when Athens was going to invade Syracuse the Syracusians asked Sparta for help.  Had to do with same ancient blood lines.  Anyhow the Spartans agreed and brought their secret sandwich the BLT and taught the Syracusans how to make them, well protecting this recipe was critical and they beat the Athenians.  Don‚Äôt bother googling this info it‚Äôs been passed down word to mouth for generations, my Yiya told me.

Garlic cheese bread, hamburgers (Mike and Amy burger), fries, all the best pastas you can imagine are here and are so good.  I am not a paid spokesman but have a well educated palate and know great food.  I read a review where someone said it didn‚Äôt look clean, I don‚Äôt agree.  It looks perfect.</Review>

<Text>I've lived in three states- Colorado, California, and where Chick-fil-A was founded, Georgia.  I've been to my fair share of Chick-fil-A's and this one stands out from the rest for being absolutely awful.  Starting with the drive-thru line, it takes at least 10 minutes to get your food even with a couple cars in front of you, while the CFA's I know crank out 15-20 cars in that same time frame.  Inside, the service us just as slow and the employees just seem to be there and not really care about what their actual job is.  But I can't pin it on them, it starts with management, specifically the operator.  I interviewed for a job here as well, and surprise, in typical fashion they wouldnt even get back to me and even when they did they'd string me along saying they'd get back to me.  I eventually talked to the operator and she lied TO MY FACE telling me that they currently were not hiring, which was a complete lie since you don't interview someone if you're not hiring, not to mention there are signs all around the interior saying they ARE hiring.  Abysmal management always sets the tone for a workplace and that's why this Chick-fil-A is so bad at even the basics, they barely even say "my pleasure."  This place is the exact opposite of every standard Chick-fil-A sets, if corporate found out about this place they would have a field day with that operator.<//Text>< resp>
None< /resp>

< rate>
2</rate>
< text>
Waiting for a chicken sandwich should not be like waiting at the DMV.  Unfortunately, such is an accurate comparison  of my experience at Auburn Chic Fil A  on November 11th.  Auburn is a small town, and lately has had an increase in the saturation of fast food restaurants. Word travels fast, and if this business doesn't get it together, they won't last long.

It took 32 minutes to get my (very small) order. The amount of incompetence was overwhelming.  I got the overall impression the staff were having a bad day... everyone looked confused . It wasn't even busy (after lunch, I ordered at 2:31pm ).As I sat waiting, I had a chance to observe the other customers. They were just as frustrated as I was, to the point that some were telling customers coming through the door to not bother ordering. People were also getting wrong orders left and right. After 25 minutes, I formally complained at the front register ...

I run a business. I know that you BEND OVER BACKWARDS to make up a mistake to a customer, because business is about relationships, not numbers. Seemingly, Chick Fil A Auburn has yet to learn this.

I was not offered a refund.
I was not offered free food.
I was given a passing, half- hearted apology.

Make no mistake, I enjoy this food chain. But I don't want this experience again, and certainly wouldn't wish it on my friends and family either. Manager on duty was 'Justice' I believe.  Friendly, but incapable of keeping the ship from sinking, so to speak.  Shout out to an older gentleman, 'Steve' who was at least attempting to smooth things over. Hope things get better here... I'll check back in a few months.<//text>
< user_name>
Isaac Humber<//user_name>
